<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2027] Minor 64-bit and NOMINMAX issues in C++ library</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2027</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TNonblockingServer and THttpServer have size_t -&amp;gt; uint32_t truncations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;TZlibTransport calls std::min without enclosing it in parens.  This is a really minor issue, since we technically build with NOMINMAX in the environment (which fixes the problem), but I have a strange personal goal of being able to build without setting NOMINMAX.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;64-bit.  Windows without NOMINMAX set.&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
